# Running the Application

## Introduction

The OptiCrop application was successfully executed using the Flask framework. The application provides a web-based interface where users can enter soil nutrient values and environmental parameters to obtain crop recommendations.

## Steps to Run

1. Open the project in Visual Studio Code.
2. Open the integrated terminal.
3. Navigate to the Epic 5 project folder.
4. Execute the command:

python app.py

5. Open the browser using:

http://127.0.0.1:5000

6. Enter the required input values.
7. Click the **Predict Best Crop** button.
8. View the recommended crop displayed on the screen.

## Testing

The application was tested using sample agricultural data from the Crop Recommendation dataset. The system successfully predicted the appropriate crop based on the provided values.

## Output

The application displays the recommended crop in a highlighted result section after processing the input values.

## Conclusion

The OptiCrop application was successfully executed and demonstrated accurate crop prediction using the trained Logistic Regression model.
